, you'll…\n\nLead your first end-to-end design project for Shipper TMS (or Trust & Safety) , from problem framing to delivery in collaboration with PM and engineers.\nConduct at least 3 user research sessions (interviews, usability tests, or surveys) and share insights with the team.\nPrototype and validate one concept using AI-powered design tools (e.g., Figma Make, Lovable, GPT workflows).\nContribute updates to the Super Dispatch Design System, ensuring alignment with other squads.\nShare your first design review presentation with cross-functional stakeholders (PM, EM, CPO).\n\nWithin 6 months, you'll…\n\nOwn multiple design initiatives within Shipper TMS, balancing short-term usability fixes with longer-term workflow improvements.\nDrive measurable impact (e.g., improved task completion, higher adoption of a feature, or reduced support tickets).\nMentor or support a peer designer by reviewing work, sharing feedback, or contributing to design critiques.\nHelp refine and scale experimentation practices in the squad, encouraging quick prototyping and data-driven iteration.\n\nWithin 12 months, you'll…\n\nBecome the design lead for Shipper TMS (or Trust & Safety), driving the vision for shipper/broker workflows in collaboration with PM and EM.\nShape and deliver at least one strategic feature or workflow redesign that significantly improves customer outcomes.\nPartner with the analytics and product teams to define and track design KPIs tied to business and user success.\nContribute thought leadership within Super Dispatch (e.g., leading design workshops, sharing best practices, or writing internal playbooks).\nBe recognized as a trusted partner by leadership and peers for your design impact, collaboration, and customer-first mindset.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nGreat Culture - We strive for transparency and you'll work with like minded highly motivated people excited about solving complex problems\nRemote First Culture - We're a 100% distributed team!\nGym/Wellness Stipend 